                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of the Army Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the Secretary of
                        War</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-08">September 8,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for the Secretary of War</hi>
                </p>
                <p>As a result of years of Fascist and Nazi rule and the destruction resulting from
                    the battles on its soil, I understand that the supply situation in Italy is
                    critical.</p>
                <p>This situation should be corrected as effectively and as quickly as possible.</p>
                <p>The War Department should, therefore, take immediate action to make available the
                    additional essential civilian supplies and shipping necessary to remedy this
                    condition.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin</hi> D. <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
